structure.unit: STATE LIBRARIES -- LIBRARIANS -- STATE ARCHIVES AND RECORDS

law.text:
As used in KRS 171.810 to 171.814:
"Commission" means the Kentucky African-American Heritage Commission.
"Council" means the Underground Railroad Advisory Council established in KRS 171.814.
"Underground Railroad" means the escape of African-American slaves from or through Kentucky.
law.history: Created 2003 Ky. Acts ch. 11, sec. 1, effective June 24, 2003.
